Chat GPT 5 was not for use, it was to get rid of free users all along.

Chat GPT 5 was never created to be a new, more performative model, it was used to get rid of free users, see, it required too much money for them to allow free users on it.

Their first move was to allow only pro users to be able to continue using chat gpt4, with a wait and see politics for plus users.

My bet is: free users will be stuck to the "new" model, that is unusable,

 So they'll switch to an other IA, they'll be a burden for the other company and open IA will deal mostly only with pro and plus users.

To sum up: it was the plan all along for chat GPT 5 to be shitty and unusable all along, their real aim by releasing it was to get rid of free users, and see how the plus users would react to it.
